The '''streaked saltator''' ('''''Saltator striatipectus''''') is a species of [[saltator]] in the family [[Thraupidae]]. It is found in [[Colombia]], [[Costa Rica]], [[Ecuador]], [[Guadeloupe]], [[Panama]], [[Peru]], and [[Venezuela]].

Measuring {{cvt|18|cm|in}},<ref name=BOP/> this species has plain olive green upperparts and olive streaked underparts. Its face features a large black bill, a broken white eyering and whitish supercilium.

